  9. Account Lockout
  Definition

  Account Lockout temporarily disables an account after several failed login attempts.

  Example:

  Wrong Password

  ↓

  5 Attempts

  ↓

  Account Locked

  ↓

  30 Minutes
  Advantages
  Stops brute force attacks
  Slows attackers
  Disadvantages

  Attackers may intentionally lock users out of their own accounts (a form of Denial-of-Service).

  Best Practices
  Use unique passwords.
  Enable MFA.
  Use a password manager.
  Never reuse passwords.
  Be cautious of suspicious emails.
  Verify website URLs.
  Never share OTPs.
